First Department,

April, 1942.

(April 2, 1942.) The People of the State of New York, Respondent, v. Louis Plantamura, Appellant.

The guilt of the defendant of the crime charged was not established beyond a reasonable doubt. Judgment unanimously reversed and information dismissed. (People v. Biocehio, 259 App. Div. 267.) Present — Martin, P. J., Townley, Dore, Cohn and Callahan, JJ.
